Comments . The sculpture of the disc of the clypeus in females is variable; in some specimens the reticulation is stronger, others have sparser punctation (i= 1–1.5 d) sometimes even with an impunctate area medially. This species has the weakest microsculpture of the mesoscutum and mesoscutellum in the genus. This small bee seems to be most easily collected using pan traps (for pan trap methodology see
Droege, 2005
).
